2 unit(s) Beyond Meat®
¾ cup Jasmine Rice
170 g Coleslaw Cabbage Mix
56 g Edamame
1 unit(s) Green Onion
2 tbsp Ginger Sauce
2 tbsp Seasoned Rice Vinegar
2 tbsp Spicy Mayo
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
9 g Sesame Seeds
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Once water is almost at a boil, using a strainer, rinse rice until water runs clear.
Add rice and edamame to the boiling water, then reduce heat to low. Cover and cook until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, 14-15 min.
Remove from heat. Set aside, still covered.

Meanwhile, heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high heat.
While the pan heats, thinly slice green onion.
When hot, add Beyond Meat® to the dry pan. Cook for 5-6 min, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy.**
Add broth concentrate, half the vinegar, 1 1/2 tbsp (3 tbsp) ginger sauce and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) water. Cook, stirring often, until sauce thickens slightly, 1-2 min.

Add coleslaw cabbage mix, half the green onions, remaining vinegar and 1/2 tbsp (1 tbsp) ginger sauce to a medium bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.

Fluff rice with a fork, then stir in half the sesame seeds.
Divide rice between bowls. Top with Beyond Meat® mixture and slaw.
Drizzle with spicy mayo and sprinkle green onions and remaining sesame seeds over top.

If you've opted to get Beyond Meat®, cook for 5-6 min, in the same way as the beef, breaking up patties into smaller pieces, until crispy.** Disregard instructions to drain excess fat.